        <Note_Text>Physical formats, objects, digital information, or other non-material human constructs by which specific information may be recorded or conveyed. For example, books, leaflets, or audiotapes; or in computing, the primary components of an information artifact are information systems and procedures related to the artifact.</Note_Text>
